SW3. The entire alignment and various\npartitions facilitate quantitative analyses of name/meaning dissociation,\nrevealing that approximately one in three paired name usages across treatments\nis not reliable - in the sense of the same name identifying congruent taxonomic\nmeanings. We conclude with an optimistic outlook for logic-based provenance\ntools in next-generation biodiversity and phylogeny data platforms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Dec 2014 19:08:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 9 Dec 2014 16:19:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-12-12"}
