 momenta $p_T$. The\n$v_n$ coefficients show characteristic patterns consistent with hydrodynamical\nexpansion of the matter produced in the collisions. For each harmonic $n$, a\nmodified valence quark number $n_q$ scaling plotting $v_n/(n_q)^{n/2}$ versus\n${\\rm KE}_T/n_q$ is observed to yield a single curve for all the measured\nparticle species for a broad range of transverse kinetic energies ${\\rm KE}_T$.\nA simultaneous blast wave model fit to the observed particle spectra and\n$v_n(p_T)$ coefficients identifies spatial eccentricities $s_n$ at freeze-out,\nwhich are much smaller than the initial-state geometric values.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Dec 2014 19:52:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 10 Aug 2016 22:47:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-13"}
