d momentum, and are of fundamental importance for feedback\nstudies. We show how the ASTRO-H observations in general can help to constrain\nnumerical models for outflows. The link to reflection and emission processes is\nalso discussed, as well as the possible relation between outflows and\nrelativistic emission lines. Finally, we discuss the prospects for other\nrelated categories of objects like BAL quasars, partially covered sources and\nCompton thick outflows.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Dec 2014 03:26:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-14"}
