 will also permit the\nrelativistically broadened reflection spectrum from the inner accretion disk to\nbe robustly studied, even in complex systems with, for example, warm absorption\nand composite soft excesses. Finally, the HXI will allow the detection and\nstudy of reverberation delays between the continuum and the Compton reflection\nhump from the inner disk.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Dec 2014 03:31:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-14"}
